Carving up Jim Kwik's (@jimkwik ) book Limitless rather quickly as we head into the long weekend. The stack of books to my right waiting to be reviewed is eyeing me with derision as I fall back on a book and beer post.

I did enjoy this double white, Tanaisie (or Tansy), from Le Naufrageur (@lenaufrageur ) though! Certified organic, this beer comes across with a Belgian flare while boasting strong Quebec ingredients, including maple syrup and Tansy (a flower I'd never heard of until today with some considering it a weed!). This might be the first double white I've tried if memory serves. 

Mulling over this quote: "The illiterate of the 21st century will not be those who cannot read and write, but those who cannot learn, unlearn and relearn." - Alvin Toffler

What are your thoughts on this one? An interesting shift away from the idea of reading/writing (obviously critical in today's age) but does make you think about how fast the world is changing. 

Cheers to the weekend everyone, hope you have a great one!
